<h1>UK High School Integration Bee</h1>

<p><strong>An official UK mathematics competition based on A-Level integration.</strong></p>

<p>
The UK High School Integration Bee is a national mathematics competition designed
to test students’ understanding of integration and their ability to apply it
creatively and logically.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Who can take part?</h2>
<p>
Recommended for Year 12–13 students, but open to all UK school students.
Participation is through schools, with supervision by an invigilator.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Competition Format</h2>

<h3>Round 1 – School Round</h3>
<ul>
  <li>20 multiple-choice questions</li>
  <li>5 answer options per question</li>
  <li>+3 for a correct answer</li>
  <li>−1 for an incorrect answer</li>
  <li>No calculators or technology permitted</li>
  <li>1 hour, completed in school under exam conditions</li>
</ul>

<p>
Tie-breaks are decided by number of correct answers. If still tied, rankings are
determined by the mean difficulty of the three hardest questions answered,
with difficulty based on question number.
</p>

<h3>National Final (In Person)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Top 10–20 students qualify</li>
  <li>Round-robin whiteboard problem-solving</li>
  <li>Top 8 progress to knockout rounds</li>
  <li>Final held in person (location to be confirmed)</li>
  <li>Total duration: approximately 2–3 hours</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Important Dates</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Website launch: early January</li>
  <li>Registration closes: 6 March</li>
  <li>Round 1: 19 March</li>
  <li>Results released: 27 March</li>
  <li>National Final: 17 April</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Awards</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Participation certificate for all students</li>
  <li>Certificate of Commendation for top 33%</li>
  <li>Best in School certificate</li>
  <li>Finalists: qualification certificate and badge</li>
  <li>Top 4: mathematics book prize</li>
  <li>Top 3: gold, silver, and bronze medals</li>
</ul>

<hr>

<h2>Practice Material</h2>
<p>
A practice Round 1 paper will be provided soon.
</p>

<hr>

<p>
Contact details and registration information coming shortly.
</p>

